                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-111-victim714 t18270531-111-viclabel574"></join>; the prisoner was my <rs id="t18270531-111-deflabel575" type="occupation">apprentice</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-111-defend713 t18270531-111-deflabel575"></join> about two years, and lived with me. On the 9th of April I missed some knives - I got an officer, and he told us where he had sold them; we went and found them there.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Is not his father a respectable man? A. Yes; I had 15l. with him; I had a good opinion of him.</p>
               <p>WM. SMITH. I am an officer. The prisoner told me where he had sold the knives. I found one in possession of a girl at the next house, and the rest with other persons.</p>
